When user asks to publish a draft:

1. Identify the draft file location under drafts/

Example:
drafts/mes/why-mes-fails.md

2. Extract category from folder name:
mes → docs/mes/posts/
dms → docs/dms/posts/
ba → docs/ba/posts/
linh-tinh → docs/linh-tinh/posts/

3. Convert markdown into HTML using template:
templates/post-template.html

4. Replace template variables:
{{TITLE}} = first line
{{DATE}} = current year
{{CONTENT}} = converted markdown paragraphs

5. Save output as:
docs/<category>/posts/<same filename>.html

6. Update category index:
docs/<category>/index.html

Insert inside:

<!-- POSTS START -->
<!-- POSTS END -->

format:

<div class="post">
<a href="posts/<filename>.html">{{TITLE}}</a>
<div class="meta">{{DATE}}</div>
</div>

7. Do not modify drafts folder.
